==Vietnamese==
===Etymology=== Ultimately from {{der|vi|zh|-}} {{ltc-l|聲}}, likely through a {{bor|vi|tai}} language (compare {{cog|th|เสียง}}) since the tonal correspondence is atypical for a direct borrowing. Cognate with {{cog|mtq|thiểng}}, {{cog|nuo|thiếng}}.
Attested as {{m|mkh-mvi|tiếng}} in the ''Dictionarium Annamiticum Lusitanum et Latinum'' (1651).
===Pronunciation=== {{vi-IPA}} * {{homophone|vi|tiến|Tiến}}
===Noun=== {{vi-noun|[[㗂]], [[𪱐]]|cls={{vi-l|cái}}, {{vi-l|thứ}}|sort=tieng}}
# [[voice]] #: {{uxi|vi|tắt '''tiếng'''|to lose one's voice}} # [[sound]] #: {{uxi|vi|'''tiếng''' súng|(sound of a) gunshot}} #: {{uxi|vi|'''tiếng''' sủa|bark (of a dog)}} # [[language]] #: {{uxi|vi|nói ba thứ '''tiếng'''|to speak three languages}} # [[reputation]] or [[renown]] #: {{uxi|vi|nổi tiếng|famous}} #: {{uxi|vi|khét tiếng|infamous; notorious}} #: {{uxi|vi|danh tiếng / tiếng tăm|reputation}} #: {{uxi|vi|tiếng thơm|fame for being a paragon|lit=fragrant fame}} #: {{ux|vi|Tiếng thơm còn mãi cho muôn đời sau.|They will forever be known by later generations as the paragon of virtue.}} # {{lb|vi|linguistics}} [[syllable]] # {{lb|vi|linguistics|colloquial}} [[dialect]] # {{lb|vi|linguistics|prosody|colloquial}} [[accent]] #: {{ux|vi|[[thằng cha|Thằng cha]] đó nói '''tiếng''' Quảng Ngãi tao không nghe được.|He speaks the Quãng Ngãi accent and I can't make sense of it.}} # {{lb|vi|colloquial}} [[hour]] #: {{ux|vi|Nó ngồi đọc truyện suốt năm '''tiếng'''.|He's been sitting there reading manga for five hours.}}
====Usage notes==== * ''tiếng'' meaning "language" is often used in compound words (eg. ''[[tiếng Anh]]'' "[[English]]") rather than as a [[free morpheme]], similar to the Chinese {{m|zh|文}} ([[Sino-Vietnamese|SV]]: ''{{m|vi|văn}}'') and {{m|ja|語}} (SV: ''[[ngữ]]''). The latter two are sometimes used in a Sino-Vietnamese manner (eg. ''[[Pháp văn]]'' "[[French]]", ''[[Hoa ngữ]]'' "[[Chinese]]"). If one wishes to refer to "language" as a [[standalone]] term in formal contexts, ''[[ngôn ngữ]]'' is used instead. In informal contexts, one may use for instance ''ba thứ tiếng'' to mean "three languages". * The word ''[[âm]]'' is used instead of ''tiếng'' to mean a sound made by a [[television]] set, a [[radio]], or another device that imitates or reproduces the sounds of other objects. ''Âm'' is also used in phonetics. * ''tiếng'' meaning "hour" is used in casual speech to refer to a '''period of time''', to avoid confusion with ''giờ''. ''giờ'' is used to refer to either a period of time or a '''point in time''' in formal context (for example, ''năm giờ'' means either "five hours" or "five o'clock"). One may also use ''tiếng {{l|vi|đồng hồ}}'' or ''giờ đồng hồ'' to refer to a period of time.
====Synonyms==== * {{sense|sound}} {{l|vi|âm}} (see [[#Usage note|usage note]] above) * {{sense|language}} {{l|vi|ngôn ngữ}}; {{l|vi|ngữ}} * {{sense|syllable}} {{l|vi|âm tiết}}; {{l|vi|vần}} * {{sense|dialect}} {{l|vi|phương ngữ}}; {{l|vi|phương ngôn}} * {{sense|accent}} {{l|vi|giọng}}; {{l|vi|khẩu âm}} * {{sense|hour}} {{l|vi|giờ}}
